
# üß† Phantom.ai ‚Äî AI Screen Upgrade Plan

**Mode:** Cursor-Style Unified Interaction
**Scope:** Workspace ‚Üí AI Execution Surface
**Architecture:** HTML / CSS / JS + PHP (localhost:8080)
**Status:** Proposed (Ready for Implementation)

---

## 1. OBJECTIVE (CLEAR)

Upgrade the existing AI interaction screen so the user can:

* Type natural language instructions
* Upload files and images directly
* Provide web URLs as context
* Receive AI responses inline (code + text)
* Allow the AI to **read and modify system options** *within defined boundaries*
* Maintain full auditability and deterministic behavior

This screen becomes the **primary AI execution interface**, similar to Cursor, but compliant with Phantom.ai constraints.

---

## 2. CORE PRINCIPLES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

* **Single unified input surface**
* **Explicit context visibility** (no hidden data)
* **AI cannot act silently**
* **All changes require human confirmation**
* **All actions logged**

---

## 3. AI SCREEN ‚Äî FUNCTIONAL LAYOUT (MINIMAL)

### A. Unified Input Panel (Top or Center)

**Purpose:** Primary command interface

**Components**

* Multiline text input
  *‚ÄúDescribe what you want the AI to do‚Ä¶‚Äù*
* Submit button (`Send to AI`)
* Keyboard shortcut (Enter / Shift+Enter)

**Behavior**

* Input is stored as a task snapshot
* Cannot be overwritten after submission (history preserved)

---

### B. Context Attachment Panel (Inline / Expandable)

**Purpose:** Cursor-style context loading

**Supported Inputs**

* üìÑ File upload (PHP, JS, CSS, JSON, MD)
* üñº Image upload (SVG, PNG, JPG)
* üåê Web URL input (read-only fetch or snapshot)
* üìÅ Project file selector (existing files)

**Controls**

* Include / Exclude toggles per item
* Remove context item before send

**Rules**

* Context is explicitly listed
* AI only sees what is checked
* Context list is logged

---

### C. AI Response Panel (Primary Output)

**Purpose:** Display AI output

**Content Types**

* Text explanation
* Code blocks (syntax highlighted)
* Structured changes (diff-style when possible)

**Controls**

* Copy
* Save to artifacts
* Send to Review
* Escalate to Copilot (if allowed)

---

### D. AI-Accessible Settings Panel (Controlled)

**Purpose:** Allow AI to optimize workflow **without breaking safety**

**Settings AI May Propose Changes To**

* AI Tier (Cheap / Mid / Copilot)
* Escalation mode (Auto / Forced)
* Context inclusion rules
* Output format (text / code / diff)
* Workflow hints (review vs generate)

**Critical Rule**

> AI **proposes**, user **approves**

**UI Mechanism**

* ‚ÄúAI Suggests Change‚Äù banner
* Accept / Reject per suggestion
* No silent changes

---

## 4. INTERACTION FLOW (AUTHORITATIVE)

```text
User Input + Context
        ‚Üì
AI Execution
        ‚Üì
AI Response Rendered
        ‚Üì
(Optional) AI Suggests Setting Changes
        ‚Üì
User Accepts / Rejects
        ‚Üì
Output Saved ‚Üí Review ‚Üí Files
```

No shortcuts. No hidden automation.

---

## 5. CURSOR PARITY FEATURES (ALLOWED)

| Feature                    | Supported | Notes                    |
| -------------------------- | --------- | ------------------------ |
| Inline AI response         | ‚úÖ         | Read-only until accepted |
| File upload                | ‚úÖ         | Explicit context         |
| Image input                | ‚úÖ         | Context only             |
| URL input                  | ‚úÖ         | Snapshot or fetch        |
| Code rewrite               | ‚úÖ         | Via accept/save          |
| Auto settings optimization | ‚ö†Ô∏è        | Proposal-only            |
| Silent changes             | ‚ùå         | Forbidden                |

---

## 6. SECURITY & AUDIT (MANDATORY)

Every AI interaction must log:

* User ID
* Timestamp
* Input text
* Context items
* AI tier used
* Suggested setting changes
* User approvals/rejections

Stored in:

```
logs/audit.log
artifacts/ai-history/
```

---

## 7. IMPLEMENTATION NOTES (LOCKED STACK)

* **HTML**

  * `<textarea>` for input
  * `<input type="file">` for uploads
  * `<input type="url">` for web context
* **JS**

  * Context manager
  * Response renderer
  * Approval gate logic
* **PHP**

  * Context validation
  * File storage
  * AI execution routing
  * Audit logging

No Node. No frameworks.

---

## 8. EFFICIENCY OPPORTUNITIES (SAFE OPTIMIZATIONS)

* Remember last context set per task
* Auto-collapse context panel after send
* Highlight changed sections in AI output
* One-click ‚ÄúSend to Review‚Äù

All optional. None implicit.

---

## 9. OUT OF SCOPE (FOR NOW)

* Real-time streaming tokens
* Background execution
* Autonomous agent loops
* Multi-user simultaneous editing

---

## 10. STATUS

‚úÖ Architecture compliant
‚úÖ Cursor-style interaction achieved
‚úÖ Security preserved
‚úÖ Audit intact
‚úÖ Ready for implementation or Copilot escalation

