# üß† Phantom.ai ‚Äî AI Self-Maintenance & Upgrade Capability

**Mode:** Controlled, Command-Driven
**Status:** Added (Architecture-Safe)
**Applies To:** AI Screen / System Layer

---

## 1. OBJECTIVE (PRECISE)

Enable Phantom.ai to **maintain, upgrade, or modify itself on explicit command**, using approved AI sources, while preserving:

* Human control
* Deterministic execution
* Full audit trail
* No silent changes
* No architecture violations

This is **assisted self-maintenance**, not autonomous mutation.

---

## 2. APPROVED AI SOURCES (LOCKED)

Phantom.ai may route maintenance tasks to **only** these sources:

| Source             | Role                               |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| **GitHub**         | Reference code, issues, PRs        |
| **GitHub Copilot** | High-tier production code          |
| **ChatGPT**        | Planning, refactors, documentation |
| **Claude Sonnet**  | Long-form reasoning, audits        |

No other models are permitted unless explicitly added later.

---

## 3. SELF-MAINTENANCE COMMAND TYPES

AI self-maintenance is **command-initiated only**.

### Supported Commands

* `Upgrade Phantom.ai dashboard`
* `Refactor review workflow`
* `Fix security issue`
* `Improve performance`
* `Align UI with SVG`
* `Update documentation`
* `Prepare migration plan`

Commands must be **explicitly typed by the user**.

---

## 4. SELF-MAINTENANCE MODE (NEW UI STATE)

### A. Maintenance Mode Toggle (System / AI Screen)

**States**

* OFF (default)
* ON (manual enable)

**Rules**

* Mode resets to OFF after task completion
* Cannot run in background
* Cannot chain commands automatically

---

### B. Maintenance Intent Declaration (Required)

Before execution, Phantom.ai must generate:

* Summary of proposed change
* Files affected
* AI source to be used
* Risk level (Low / Medium / High)
* Rollback plan

**User must approve before proceeding.**

---

## 5. EXECUTION FLOW (MANDATORY)

```text
User Command
     ‚Üì
AI Analysis (Planning Tier)
     ‚Üì
Proposed Maintenance Plan
     ‚Üì
User Approval
     ‚Üì
Execution (Approved AI Source)
     ‚Üì
Output (Diff / Files / Instructions)
     ‚Üì
Review ‚Üí Accept ‚Üí Save
```

No step may be skipped.

---

## 6. AI SOURCE ROUTING RULES

| Task Type              | Default Source |
| ---------------------- | -------------- |
| Planning / Design      | ChatGPT        |
| Code Review / Refactor | Claude Sonnet  |
| Production Code        | Copilot        |
| Research / References  | GitHub         |

User may override source **before execution**.

---

## 7. PERMITTED SELF-MODIFICATION SCOPE

AI may **propose** changes to:

* HTML / CSS / JS files
* PHP logic (non-auth first)
* Dashboard layout
* Workflow rules
* Documentation

AI may **not** modify without approval:

* Authentication system
* Audit logging
* IP lock enforcement
* Architecture constraints (PHANTOM-UI-001)

---

## 8. SAFETY BOUNDARIES (ENFORCED)

‚ùå No auto-merge
‚ùå No silent file writes
‚ùå No dependency changes
‚ùå No new tooling (Node, Vite, etc.)
‚ùå No schema changes without migration plan

‚úÖ Diff-based output only
‚úÖ Human acceptance required

---

## 9. AUDIT & TRACEABILITY (REQUIRED)

Each self-maintenance task logs:

* Command text
* AI source used
* Proposed plan
* Approved scope
* Files touched
* Outcome (accepted/rejected)

Stored under:

```
logs/maintenance.log
artifacts/self-maintenance/
```

---

## 10. UI ADDITION (MINIMAL)

Add **one** new control only:

### ‚ÄúAI Maintenance Command‚Äù Input

* Text input (single or multiline)
* Disabled unless Maintenance Mode = ON
* Clearly labeled **‚ÄúSystem Modification Command‚Äù**

No other UI expansion required.

---

## 11. EFFICIENCY BENEFITS (INTENDED)

* Faster internal upgrades
* Safer refactors
* Reduced manual repetition
* Predictable system evolution

Without sacrificing control.

---

## 12. STATUS

‚úÖ Architecture preserved
‚úÖ Security enforced
‚úÖ Human-in-the-loop guaranteed
‚úÖ Multi-AI support formalized
‚úÖ Ready for implementation

